Parking Management System
This Java-based application manages a parking lot by handling user registration, sign-ins, and vehicle tracking through automated file logging.

Core Principles
-Encapsulation: Protects user and vehicle data within private fields, allowing access only through public methods.

-Abstraction: Simplifies complex operations, such as file persistence and date-based calculations, into high-level method calls.

-Modularity: Distributes functionality across distinct classes, with User managing accounts, Slot managing vehicle details, and Parking acting as the system controller.

Data Structures: 
-HashSet: Enables high-speed user verification during registration and login.

-TreeSet: Automatically sorts parking slots based on entrance time via the Comparable interface.

-HashMap & Queue: Pairs users with their vehicles using a First-In, First-Out (FIFO) sequence for organized removal.

-ArrayList: Monitors real-time lot occupancy to track capacity and prevent overfilling.

Key Features
-Data Persistence: Records every registration and parking transaction into registers.txt and history.txt.

-Session Management: Restricts parking and removal actions to signed-in users for increased security.

VIP Integration: Categorizes users to allow for specialized parking logic based on membership status.
